message.content: This question tests knowledge about renewable energy sources. Renewable energy sources are those that can be replenished naturally and indefinitely. Options (A), (B), and (D) are all examples of renewable energy sources. Solar energy is derived from the sun and can be harnessed using solar panels. Wind energy is generated by the natural movement of air and can be captured using wind turbines. Hydropower is generated from the movement of water, such as from rivers or dams. Option (C), natural gas, is not considered a renewable energy source because it is a fossil fuel that is formed from the remains of ancient plants and animals. Once it is used up, it cannot be replenished within a reasonable human time frame. Therefore, option (C) is the correct answer.
